HI and thanks for fast answer & smart package.
well, It is very clear from the documentation use of 'root_results_path', no problem;
infact I setted a relative path to store records, and all works great;
for example I notice that "experiment id" are saved in /TestedKeys/ subdirectory;
so, I do not think it is necessary to make 'root_results_path' a required argument, 
because sometimes it might be useful to explore a shrinked space on the fly for simple e fast tasks;
then displayed scores can be enough;


my problem is that it's not clear to me which experiments are saved in 'optimizer.similar_experiments';
when I run "examples/functionality_example.py" script, not all experiments are 'saved in 'optimizer.similar_experiments';
but of course all of them are saved in 'GlobalLeaderboard.csv';
then most of the time "assert experiment.experiment_id in [_[2] for _ in optimizer.similar_experiments]" raises Expections...(then, where Hunter "compare" entryes ('cross_experiment_key',) for  current Enviroment key?

@HunterMcGushion 
 so I imagine I'll add an additional kwarg to Environment, in which you can specify whether the metric should be maximized or minimized.

Yes! will be perfect ;)

edit: I notice that only the best/worse (based on metric) model's parameters's values are displayed at the end of optimization...(then in case of 'mse' only the worse model's params are displayed);
then how it's possible  extract/visualize  parameters's values relative to the best model(or at least by specified 'experiment_id')?

